sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as Client Code<br/>(starboard-server)
    participant Repo as ConversationRepository<br/>(starboard-core)
    participant Port as StateStore Protocol<br/>(starboard-core)
    participant Impl as PostgresStateStore<br/>(starboard-server)
    participant DB as Database

    Note over Client,DB: Repository Pattern Flow

    Client->>Repo: get_or_create(user_id)
    
    Repo->>Port: load_conversation(id)
    Note over Port: Protocol defines interface<br/>not implementation
    
    Port->>Impl: (protocol satisfied)
    Impl->>DB: SELECT * FROM conversations
    DB-->>Impl: Raw data
    Impl-->>Port: Conversation (domain model)
    Port-->>Repo: Conversation
    
    Repo->>Repo: Business logic<br/>(pure domain)
    
    Repo-->>Client: Conversation (type-safe)
    
    Note over Client: Client works with<br/>domain models only.<br/>No database knowledge.
    
    Client->>Repo: add_episode(conv_id, episode)
    Repo->>Port: save_conversation(conversation)
    Port->>Impl: (protocol satisfied)
    Impl->>DB: INSERT INTO episodes
    DB-->>Impl: Success
    Impl-->>Port: conversation_id
    Port-->>Repo: conversation_id
    Repo-->>Client: Done

